493
00:24:58,328 --> 00:25:01,929
So the first thing is the lowest risk practice.

494
00:25:01,929 --> 00:25:04,369
It's that in the beginning of any video,

495
00:25:04,369 --> 00:25:07,070
whether that's a fixed length video like YouTube,

496
00:25:07,070 --> 00:25:09,310
or that's a Twitch stream,

497
00:25:09,310 --> 00:25:12,531
at the very beginning you wanna have both a text-based

498
00:25:12,531 --> 00:25:14,311
and an audible disclosure,

499
00:25:14,311 --> 00:25:19,592
at least if your video has audible content.

500
00:25:19,592 --> 00:25:23,133
In addition to that first disclosure,

501
00:25:23,133 --> 00:25:25,493
if you have a video that isn't fixed length,

502
00:25:25,493 --> 00:25:27,373
think about a live stream,

503
00:25:28,434 --> 00:25:32,015
you have two options. You can either have periodic

504
00:25:32,015 --> 00:25:35,157
disclosures, or you can have constant disclosures.

505
00:25:35,157 --> 00:25:38,578
Sort of self-explanatory, although let's talk about it.

506
00:25:38,578 --> 00:25:43,880
A periodic disclosure means every once in a while

507
00:25:43,880 --> 00:25:46,861
you have a disclosure. And you're probably thinking right

